extendedInfo.description: Take control of your finances today with PocketMoney. A powerful yet easy to use personal finance manager, PocketMoney lets you track your cash flow, understand your net worth, and improve the overall health of your finances on your iPhone, iPod Touch, or iPad, and now your Android device. The system is simple, and a minute a day using PocketMoney will help you navigate through the pitfalls of the current economy. âº Start by entering all your income and expenses as they happen across multiple accounts such as credit cards, savings, and checking accounts. PocketMoney can track thousands of transactions through many years of financial data with no performance loss. Transactions can be split across multiple categories, transferred across accounts and can also be scheduled to occur at regular intervals. âº Analyze your overall financial health by using the built-in reporting features of PocketMoney. âº Sync with PocketMoney on other Android, iOS, Windows, OS X, or Linux devices.âº If you use Quicken or MS Money, then you can export your desktop data to PocketMoney, enter data on the road, then export changes back to your desktop app via QIF files. (Quicken Essentials doesn't support QIF exports/imports.) Features Include: Accounts â Unlimited number of accounts and transactions â Accounts include credit cards, checking, overdraft, savings and more â Proven performance and responsiveness â Reconcile and rollup your accounts. â Current, future, cleared balance displays â Customized account ordering, grouping and graphics Transactionsâ Splits and Transfers â Customized transaction entry preferences â Custom filters â Repeating transactions with complex logic and notificationsâ Attach photo receipts to transactionUser Experienceâ Pick your color with themesâ Support for "Keep The Change"â Calculator Keypad for easy entry of amounts or to do calculations right in the amount field.Budgetsâ Daily, weekly, monthly, quarterly, semi-annually, annually.â Rollover budgetings.Reports â Custom reporting for Accounts, Categories, Class and Payee â In App Purchase for pie chartsInteroperability â PocketMoney Sync - lets you sync to PocketMoney on other Android, iOS, or desktop devices via local Wi-Fi.â Email and SD card backup/restore â Import - TDF, CSV, QIF, OFX/QFXâ Export - TDF, CSV, QIF, OFX/QFXUsability â Multi-currency â Password protection â Transaction searchkeywords: bank, banking, checkbook, finances, quicken, ms money, money, pocket money, savings, credit cards, personal finance, expenses, checking, checks, cash, currencies

reviews.title: Software Bom

reviews.title: I have had no problems
reviews.comment: I do not know about the previous reviews, I can only assume that whatever bugs were present have been fixed with updates.  My experience has been ported over from iOS.  This app is as good as the iOS version maybe better.  This app has always done what I need it to do, I regret trying to buy other Finance Tracking apps for android when this was what I had previously and still needed all along.  TY!
reviews.author: SEAN PHILLIPS

reviews.title: Excellent product
reviews.comment: I needed a product that all ows for transaction entry on either desktop or mobile device and that would synchronize.  This fits the bill perfectly!!
reviews.author: Collington Rowe

reviews.title: Under Android disappointing
reviews.comment: I have been using this app with my iphone for two years and really enjoyed it and recommend it. It is a nightmare since I changed to Android. Why is it so completely different and user unfriendly ? Paid a second time for just disappointment.
reviews.author: Man Min

reviews.title: Doesn\'t work
reviews.comment: On 1gig processor android 2.36 it locks up repeatedly. A 2 party account with a years data is more than it can handle. Locks up on sync and delete account. Sync, when it runs, duplicates transactions giving wrong final balance. E mailed the developer 2 weeks ago. No reply!!  With that, I\'m sure asking for my money back would be ignored too. Desk top works OK, but the style is a bit grade school. Particularly the data entry form. Uninstalled on android and reinstalled. Loads \"greyed out\", wont run. Uninstall
reviews.author: Rodger Mayer

reviews.title: iOS to Android
reviews.comment: Use this app on iOS & was a great tool. Then I switched to Android. Overall migrating the data over was easy & the usage is the same. But there is one major problem. In iOS version, you have ability to reconciled but not on Android. Reconciliation is a major feature in any expenses tracking too. You need this feature to easy balanced against the monthly statement. Without it, balancing becomes a real pain. Not sure why Android version lack this critical feature? PLEASE add this feature in next release.
reviews.author: Tri Do

reviews.title: No Problems
reviews.comment: I use PocketMoney (PM) on iPhone + iPad, + new LG Optimus G Pro running Android.  I\'m not sure what other users are doing to have such bad luck.  Data restore went smooth and quick.  I reconcile on PM for Android the way I always have on PM for iOS (by matching Cleared Balance to statement balance or online current balance).  I haven\'t made up my mind about User Interface (UI) aesthetics, but function has always been more important to me than form.  Big plus for ability to back up to sd card.
reviews.author: Jason Weaver

reviews.title: Very useful app

reviews.title: Best personal finance program
reviews.comment: I have used PM on PalmOS and iOS, and now Android. It does everything I want (and more). Thanks to the dev for supporting several platforms consistently. You help me get my finances under control!  PS: thanks to the synch server, moving data from my iPhone to android was effortless and well worth type extra dollar.
